Bugfix: Prevent trashbin restore from overwriting an existing file

Restoring a file or folder from the trashbin to a location that already held a
different file silently overwrote (and thereby destroyed) the existing target.
The WebDAV restore path deleted the pre-existing destination before the restore
ran, so an earlier guard inside the restore routine never took effect. The DAV
layer now refuses such a restore with "403 Forbidden" before anything is
deleted, leaving the existing target untouched.

https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/35974
